<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Nuelaan doAevum:
[B]Excuse me very much.

I did *not* breeze in here with a twink and tell you to not play your charcter.

Read. What. I. Wrote.

--quote--
After all, these other players reason; why would one play a core class if you didn't want to be involved in guild events?
--endquote--

Some of you have clerics started 'back in the day'.  That's fine.  Lots of people have characters they kicked up in the first half of '99, back when Kunark wasn't even a rumor.

That aside, clerics and enchanters are *CORE* character classes.  Verant has designed the *entire* game to hinge on their presence.  Anything except the occasional overland areas requires the presence of *at least* a cleric, and usually the enchanter too.

When a guildmember does a survey or whatever of who's online, they turn up so many tanks, so many casters, yadda yadda; then they realise only two clerics and one enc are online.  Or one clr and two encs.  Or some other number that basically results in "not enough to go around".  They're excited, thinking they can go do game stuff with the guild cleric/enc.

So to those other guild people, it's disappointing.  It's not your fault you're not helping them, and it's not their fault they need your class to get anything done.  Verant has designed the game thus and shows no signs of changing it.  Unless and until xp_group_oo1 or raid_group_003 get that cleric, they = nada.

So it strikes me as extremely odd that a core class player would be offended that people desire their character to be present.

I mean, yeah you didn't know the entire world of Norrath revolved around you when you started, but surely you've figured that out in the 2+ years the game's been out?  So, this isn't a new thing; people asking you if you're available for a group/raid.  It should be a regular occurance.  It is for my cleric, I get contacted regularly to find out what I'm doing; many of the tanks I've played with are always interested to get back into a group with me.

But as I said, do whatever you like.  But I stand by my other original statement as well.  If you simply want to log into the game and run around hanging out and talking and such, I strongly recommend a druid.  They have all the travel spells, have speed spells, buff good, and can even heal and nuke/dot.  In short, they're the perfect self-contained class to port to GFay and sell some stuff, then port to West Commons to sell some more, then port down to Ferrott to pick up a guildie left by the last raid, etc...  Druids are the perfect 'hanging' class, because you can hang and not be tied to the one zone (like you are as a walking class, esp tanks).  So you can hang out wherever you like, including with your friends when they turn up; insta port plus maybe a run for a zone or two sometimes, and you can hang out with whoever it is, easily.

Just so some of you touchy "people" know, the above is not a slam on either clerics or druids, or even on old school vs other school players, or 'powergamerz/hardcore players' vs 'casual' either.

It's just the way the game is.  Clerics = uber needed.  Druids = way useful for doing solo stuff.  Don't yell at me, yell at Verant.

Of course, the 'needed' part applied to standard nice people; if you think I'm talking about helping out the losers who send you tells out of the blue that go like "d00d I died, kin u rz me" or people that walk up and say "buff plz", think again.

[This message has been edited by Dalur - Veeshan (edited 04-13-2001).][/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
